# Plan: `sentry cli defaults` Command

## Summary

Implement `sentry cli defaults` ŌĆö a single command for viewing and managing persistent CLI defaults. Consolidate storage from the dead `defaults` single-row table to the `metadata` KV table. Add persistent telemetry opt-out and `DO_NOT_TRACK` support.

## Command UX

```bash
sentry cli defaults                       # Show all current defaults
sentry cli defaults org my-org            # Set default organization
sentry cli defaults project my-proj       # Set default project
sentry cli defaults telemetry on          # Set telemetry (on/off/yes/no/true/false/1/0)
sentry cli defaults url https://...       # Set default Sentry URL (self-hosted)
sentry cli defaults org                   # Show just that default's value
sentry cli defaults org --clear           # Clear a specific default (no confirmation)
sentry cli defaults --clear               # Clear ALL defaults (needs --yes/-y/--force/-f or TTY prompt)
```

## Architecture: Single Command (Not Route Map)

Stricli receives `["org", "my-org"]` as variadic positional args via `kind: "array"`. Recognized keys: `org`, `organization`, `project`, `telemetry`, `url`.

## Storage Consolidation: Drop `defaults` Table ŌåÆ Metadata KV

The `defaults` table is never written by production code. All defaults move to `metadata`:

| Default | Metadata key | Values |
|---------|-------------|--------|
| org | `defaults.org` | org slug string |
| project | `defaults.project` | project slug string |
| telemetry | `defaults.telemetry` | `"on"` / `"off"` |
| url | `defaults.url` | URL string |

`metadata.key` is already `PRIMARY KEY` ŌåÆ implicit unique index, O(log n) lookups.

## Telemetry Priority Chain

```
1. SENTRY_CLI_NO_TELEMETRY=1   ŌåÆ disabled  (existing, highest)
2. DO_NOT_TRACK=1               ŌåÆ disabled  (new, consoledonottrack.com)
3. metadata "defaults.telemetry" ŌåÆ on/off   (new, persistent)
4. Default                      ŌåÆ enabled   (lowest)
```

## URL Priority Chain

```
1. SENTRY_HOST env var          (highest)
2. SENTRY_URL env var
3. .sentryclirc [defaults] url  (sets SENTRY_URL via env shim)
4. metadata "defaults.url"      (new ŌĆö applied in preloadProjectContext)
5. https://sentry.io            (default)
```

Applied in `preloadProjectContext()` after `applySentryCliRcEnvShim()` by writing to `env.SENTRY_URL` if unset. Same mechanism as `.sentryclirc` ŌĆö no changes to `getConfiguredSentryUrl()`.

